  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Beekeeping and Honey Production to Build Sustainable Livelihoods in Debed Village</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will improve the socio-economic situation of 75 families in the Armenian village of Deved through the provision of beehives and training. Heifer&#x2019;s intervention in this community came after the completion of a needs assessment, the result of which, beekeeping and cattle breeding were identified as the best strategies to reduce the community&#x2019;s poverty and unemployment levels and to prevent emigration from the village. In the spring of 2010, 25 families will receive 100 beehives (four beehives per family). In the spring of 2012, the original families will Pass on the Gift of 100 beehives to 25 new families, who will then Pass on the Gift of 100 beehives to 25 more families in the same community in 2014. All of the participants will be trained in beekeeping, honey production and marketing.</narrative>
  </description>
